==English==

===Etymology 1===
Noun from {{inh|en|ang|wund}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*wundō}}. Verb from {{inh|en|ang|wundian}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*wundōną}}. Indo-European cognates include {{cog|sq|unë|t=piece of a broken pot, splinter}}.

